			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Been away a while, but this caught my eye.  It's stupid!!  There are many reasons why a player might want to drop coins on the ground.  As a newbie, I loved it.  For those hapless folks who happen to get caught up in a scam -- I feel for you, but them's the breaks. :)<BR>
I have not heard of any problems with this particular scam.  Some have brought up the idea that Verant wants to discourage twinking.  Most people who want to twink have the people resources needed to accomplish that.  But aside from that, if you've slogged your way into the upper levels and want to start a new character, you should be afforded any easy way to transfer items to that new character -- you earned it.<BR>
Fix the problem leading to the scam, but don't make coin drops impossible -- there are too many good reasons for being able to drop coin.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
