	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Terrible, terrible idea.<BR>
<BR>
Players should be left with the choice to drop their own coins. Monks have already stated how this patch will inconvenience their own gameplay when fighting mobs.<BR>
<BR>
Recent Messages of the Day have warned us to be careful when trading with others, and now Verant pushes through something which FORCES us into that position.<BR>
<BR>
To the poster who believes passing money between same-account characters isn't roleplaying, you are just narrow minded mate.<BR>
I'm trying to run a medical rescue service across Norrath with three characters all on the same team. I am no good at earning plat, so if one character manages to amass some, and the others need it to do their job better, I want to be able to drop some money off, logout, login, and my low level healer is little bit better off.<BR>
<BR>
Just give us who are willing to take the risk, a confirmation box, like you do with items to be destroyed. Instead of fragging with players who are trying to play the game.<BR>
<BR>
Yavinelf - 22 Ranger (Rescue Ranger, LOIO)<BR>
Yavscout - 14 Druid (Scout, Paineel)<BR>
Debgate  - 5 Shaman (Halas agent, err...Halas)<BR>
SUREFALL PARAMEDICS
